New Records: Harry Kane took his England tally to a record-extending 68 goals
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored both goals in the 2-0 victory
Trent Alexander-Arnold made five or six stunning passes that carved the Finns open
Lukas Hradecky made several fine saves to deny Harry Kane
Pre-Game Insights: Interim head coach Lee Carsley made his Wembley bow
Harry Kane marked his 100th senior international appearance
Post-Match Reflections: England's win was their second under interim manager Lee Carsley
England's win puts them joint top of their Nations League group with Greece
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played on a wet London night
The match was held at Wembley
Harry Kane received a golden cap before kick-off and sported a pair of dazzling golden boots
Others: Trent Alexander-Arnold was England's best player with an 8/10 rating
